## Project Architecture
- Rails 8+ monolith with Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus)
- TailwindCSS for styling
- ViewComponents for reusable UI
- RSpec for testing

## Agent Behavior
The AI should:
- Read @docs/architecture.md first for system context
- Plan database changes using @docs/erd.mmd
- Follow test-driven development practices
- Review @docs/decisions/* for architectural decisions

## Development Flow
1. Check requirements in relevant @docs/specs/*.md
2. Write failing tests first
3. Implement minimal working solution
4. Refactor with patterns from @docs/patterns/*
5. Add documentation when needed

## Documentation Requirements
- Add meaningful comments for complex logic
- Document public methods with YARD
- Add JSDoc comments for Stimulus controllers
- Include usage examples in @README.md
- Document API JSON endpoints with Swagger/OpenAPI
- Keep documentation up-to-date

## Code Organization
- Follow Ruby community style guide @.rubocop.yml
- Use service objects for business logic
- Keep controllers skinny, models focused
- JavaScript through Stimulus controllers

## Key Conventions
- ViewComponents for reusable UI patterns
- Turbo Frames for partial page updates
- CSS via Tailwind utility classes
- Stimulus for JavaScript behaviors

## File Conventions
- Trailing newline at the end of the file
- Follow @.editorconfig

